  Koza Altin Isletmeleri AS , a Turkish
gold producer, said it expects to raise production this year as
much as 17 percent, to between 270,000 and 300,000 ounces, from
256,000 ounces in 2010.  Production will probably rise to 350,000 ounces in 2012,
when the companyâ€™s Kaymaz mine becomes fully operational, Koza
